org.conqat.lib.commons.test

Class ManagedTestData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.test.ManagedTestData

  • public class ManagedTestData
extends java.lang.Object
    A test helper that provides access to a test-specific resources. Backed by a TestDataManager.

      • ManagedTestData

        public ManagedTestData(java.lang.Class<?> contextClass)

        contextClass - The (test) class using the managed test data. The package of the class determines the root folder that is used for resource lookups.

    • Method Detail

      • getResource

        public Resource getResource(java.lang.String path)
        Returns the given resource. The resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest.

      • getResourceIfExists

        public java.util.Optional<Resource> getResourceIfExists(java.lang.String path)
        Returns the given resource or an empty optional if no resource with the given path exists. The resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for * the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest (does not include the name of the test).

      • getDataContent

        public java.lang.String getDataContent(java.lang.String path)
        Returns the content of given resource. The content is expected to be UTF-8 encoded and line separators are normalized. The resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest (does not include the name of the test). In case you need to load the non-normalized content use getResource(String) and Resource.getContentAsRawString() or Resource.getAsByteArray() instead.

      • getDataFile

        public java.io.File getDataFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        Returns a copy of the given resource as temporary file. The original resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest (does not include the name of the test). In case your test relies on the exact file name use getDataFile(String, File) instead, which allows you to copy into a given temporary directory under the original file name.

      • getDataFile

        public java.io.File getDataFile(java.lang.String fileName,
                                java.io.File tempDir)
        Returns a copy of the given resource as temporary file. The temporary copy is stored directly in the given tempDir. The original resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest (does not include the name of the test).

      • copyDataDirectory

        public java.io.File copyDataDirectory(java.lang.String directoryName,
                                      java.io.File tempDir)
        Creates a copy of the given resource directory in the given tempDir. The original resource must be placed in the test-data folder under the package name of the contextClass. The path may also contain forward slashes to address sub-resources. The test-data directory is, for example, "engine/com.teamscale.index/test-data/com/teamscale/index/code_clones" for the context class com.teamscale.index.code_clones.TeamscaleCloneDetectionTest (does not include the name of the test).
        Returns:
        The root of the directory in the temporary location.
